[FILE:340:descriptions/desc.single]
This module implements so-called "guards". A guard is something (usually an
object) that "guards" a resource, ensuring that it is cleaned up when
expected.  Specifically, this module supports two different types of
guards: guard objects, which execute a given code block when destroyed, and
scoped guards, which are tied to the scope exit.


